igerator until ready to use (jam will thicken as it cools)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Eggs"},{"content":"Grease 4 egg rings with oil and set aside. Line Varoma tray with a piece of wet and well-wrung baking paper, ensuring paper goes all the way to the edges. Place water into mixing bowl, then place Varoma into position and insert Varoma tray."},{"content":"Place egg rings onto baking paper and crack 1 egg into each ring. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>8-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until eggs are cooked to your liking."},{"content":"To serve, slice bagels in half horizontally, spread with bacon jam and top with an egg."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This recipe can serve up to 12 people at once. Simply repeat step 14 and cook as many eggs as you require. Serve any leftover bagels within 2 days.","Bacon jam and bagels can easily be prepared ahead of time for a quick and easy weekend breakfast.","Bacon jam is a perfect condiment on toasted cheese sandwiches, burgers, cheese platters or even pancakes."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","3h 20m","4 portions"]}